    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Import your `custom.py` into your project.\r\n\r\n*Don't have it, or it doesn't work? That's ok! Copy the code from* <a href=\"https://studio.code.org/projects/pythonlab/lEeO0M85P_A_B2Jcx0d2yC2yibkCG10AF_gD4ioh5Ws/view\" target=\"_blank\">***here***</a> *and paste it into a new file in your project.*\r\n\r\n2. In `custom.py`, write the `move_if_can_move(this_painter)` function. Inside this function:\r\n\r\n   * Use an `if` statement to check if the `Painter` can move\r\n   \r\n   * If true, move the `Painter` forward\r\n\r\n3. Write another function called `paint_diagonal(this_painter, color)`\r\n\r\n   * If the `Painter` is facing east, paint, call your `move_if_can_move(this_painter)` function, call your `turn_right(this_painter)` function, then move again\r\n   \r\n   * If the `Painter` is facing south, paint, call your `move_if_can_move(this_painter)` function, turn left, then move again\r\n\r\n4. Save `custom.py` to your Backpack.\r\n\r\n5. In `main.py`, import your functions.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfrom custom import function_name, function_name, function_name\r\n```\r\n\r\n6. Use your functions to collect the paint from all the paint buckets.\r\n\r\n   *Hint: You may need to call `paint_diagonal()` inside a `while` loop to continue painting while the `Painter` can move.*\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/ffd3210005c7d7b2b205fa35c8c88aea-choiceD.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nUse the UMPIRE strategy to help you program this solution:\r\n\r\n* **U**nderstand: What's the goal? What functions and conditional statements do I need? \r\n\r\n* **M**ake a plan: What code will go in the functions and conditional statements?\r\n\r\n* **P**roduce: Create the functions and conditional statements.\r\n\r\n* **I**nspect: Run it -- does it work as expected?\r\n\r\n * **R**efine: Revise your code as needed.\r\n\r\n* **E**xplain: How did using a conditional statement make your program work as needed?",
